[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 5.455,
        "duration": 1.42
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 6.875,
        "duration": 2.608
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s prepare the ingredients.",
        "start": 16.839,
        "duration": 2.774
    },
    {
        "text": "Chop up the onion into fine pieces.",
        "start": 20.651,
        "duration": 2.776
    },
    {
        "text": "Grate the naga-imo yam with a grater.",
        "start": 38.304,
        "duration": 2.866
    },
    {
        "text": "For the tsukune sauce, ",
        "start": 46.313,
        "duration": 1.638
    },
    {
        "text": "combine the soy sauce, sake, ",
        "start": 47.951,
        "duration": 2.727
    },
    {
        "text": "mirin, ",
        "start": 53.019,
        "duration": 1.233
    },
    {
        "text": "water ",
        "start": 56.954,
        "duration": 1.01
    },
    {
        "text": "and sugar.",
        "start": 60.39,
        "duration": 1.838
    },
    {
        "text": "Mix the sauce thoroughly.",
        "start": 65.101,
        "duration": 1.974
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s combine the ground meat mixture.",
        "start": 68.195,
        "duration": 3.362
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the salt to the ground chicken ",
        "start": 72.193,
        "duration": 2.345
    },
    {
        "text": "and knead it until the meat begins to look smooth ",
        "start": 77.215,
        "duration": 3.411
    },
    {
        "text": "and turn kind of gooey.",
        "start": 80.626,
        "duration": 1.858
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the onion, ",
        "start": 88.985,
        "duration": 1.754
    },
    {
        "text": "beaten egg, ",
        "start": 93.9,
        "duration": 1.235
    },
    {
        "text": "naga-imo yam, ",
        "start": 99.718,
        "duration": 1.369
    },
    {
        "text": "grated ginger ",
        "start": 104.448,
        "duration": 1.387
    },
    {
        "text": "and potato starch.",
        "start": 108.712,
        "duration": 1.556
    },
    {
        "text": "Knead the mixture ",
        "start": 113.661,
        "duration": 1.053
    },
    {
        "text": "until the ingredients blend in completely with the chicken.",
        "start": 114.714,
        "duration": 3.979
    },
    {
        "text": "Put the vegetable oil into a pan ",
        "start": 127.071,
        "duration": 2.856
    },
    {
        "text": "and coat it evenly.",
        "start": 131.765,
        "duration": 1.79
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, with your hand, ",
        "start": 138.972,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "squeeze some of the mixture into a small ball ",
        "start": 141.042,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "and spoon it onto the pan.",
        "start": 144.722,
        "duration": 2.137
    },
    {
        "text": "Do the same for the rest of the chicken mixture.",
        "start": 149.315,
        "duration": 3.296
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, turn on the burner.",
        "start": 155.671,
        "duration": 2.138
    },
    {
        "text": "Fry the tsukune on medium heat.",
        "start": 159.819,
        "duration": 2.621
    },
    {
        "text": "When they have browned thoroughly, ",
        "start": 166.321,
        "duration": 2.404
    },
    {
        "text": "flip the pieces over.",
        "start": 168.725,
        "duration": 1.842
    },
    {
        "text": "Reduce the heat to low ",
        "start": 174.547,
        "duration": 2.087
    },
    {
        "text": "and cook the inside.",
        "start": 179.143,
        "duration": 1.604
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, mix the sauce again ",
        "start": 186.733,
        "duration": 2.592
    },
    {
        "text": "and pour it into the pan.",
        "start": 189.325,
        "duration": 1.887
    },
    {
        "text": "Reduce the sauce until thickened.",
        "start": 192.984,
        "duration": 2.338
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, flip the pieces over, coating them with the sauce.",
        "start": 196.161,
        "duration": 4.246
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn off the burner ",
        "start": 210.287,
        "duration": 1.721
    },
    {
        "text": "and place the tsukune onto a plate.",
        "start": 215.102,
        "duration": 2.377
    },
    {
        "text": "Sprinkle on the sansho pepper powder to taste.",
        "start": 223.412,
        "duration": 3.323
    },
    {
        "text": "Tsukune may also be  grilled, deep-fried or simmered.",
        "start": 228.56,
        "duration": 4.498
    },
    {
        "text": "They are used in a variety of Japanese dishes.",
        "start": 233.226,
        "duration": 3.674
    },
    {
        "text": "If you can get a fresh egg intended to be eaten raw, ",
        "start": 237.286,
        "duration": 4.197
    },
    {
        "text": "break the yolk and dip the tsukune into it.",
        "start": 241.483,
        "duration": 3.31
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s a good idea to store the boiled tsukune in the freezer ",
        "start": 250.895,
        "duration": 4.23
    },
    {
        "text": "so that you can easily prepare them when needed. ",
        "start": 255.125,
        "duration": 3.561
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen.",
        "start": 258.922,
        "duration": 1.82
    }
]